    correct_answer:"A proxy fetches content on behalf of the client -- no direct connection between internal machine and external host ever exists",
    explanation:"A proxy firewall: the internal client's connection terminates at the proxy. The proxy makes its own separate request to the external server and returns the result. Benefits: internal IPs hidden from internet, can filter by URL/content/user auth, can cache pages. Not a true firewall; creates a single point that must be trusted.",
