    explanation:"Pass-the-Hash: Windows NTLM authentication accepts the hash directly -- plaintext password never needed. An attacker with a captured NTLM hash can authenticate to ANY other Windows machine that accepts that user account. Primary defences: (1) Credential Guard (isolates LSASS in Hyper-V container). (2) SMB signing. (3) LAPS (unique local admin passwords). (4) Migrate from NTLM to Kerberos.",
