    explanation:"TLS Chain of Trust: website has a certificate signed by an intermediate CA. That intermediate CA's certificate is signed by a root CA. The root CA's public key is pre-installed in your OS/browser. Browser decrypts the CA's signature on the certificate using the pre-installed root CA public key. If it decrypts correctly, the real CA signed it. Self-signed certs always trigger browser warnings -- no CA signed them.",
